author: AccessWDUN staff
title: Commerce rolls over Providence
text:
Saturday October 17th, 2015 3:27AM Posted 7:43AM on Saturday 17th October 2015 ( 4 hours from now ) Commerce rolls over Providence By AccessWDUN staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 8: Surprises abound in wild night of prep football VIDEO: Rabun County routs Union County in top 10 showdown, 49-3 
COMMERCE — Caleb Brooks had 133 yards rushing and scored twice despite just six carries to lead Commerce to a 45-0 win over Providence Christian Friday night at Tiger Stadium. 
The Tigers (4-3, 3-2 Region 8-A) pounded out 352 yards on the ground and took control early scoring 21 points each in the first and second quarters. 
J’various Wood scored on a 10-yard run to start things off for Commerce and Cole Chancey followed moments later with a 2-yard touchdown run for a 14-0 lead. Brooks then scored his first touchdown on a 41-yard run to cap a 21-0 first quarter. 
The Tigers continued the onslaught as Will Thomas scored a 34-yard run with Brooks getting his second touchdown of the game on a 10-yard run midway through the period. Trevonta Williford capped the 42-points first half returning a Providence fumble 43 yards for a touchdown. 
Andres Salgado capped the scoring with a 34-yard field goal in the third quarter. 
The Tigers held Providence Christian (0-7, 0-4) to just 96 yards rushing and 13 yards pass for the game. 
Commerce next will travel to Towns County next week in another 8-A battle. Associated Categories : Sports , High School Sports , Friday Game Night Associated Tags : High school football, Commerce football © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
